In addition to @civtorm1710&#39;s answer:
 - If you are using `spring-rabbit`, don&#39;t care about the retry or auto-recovery things, spring will handle the connection lost issue very well;
 - By default RabbitMQ client will retry at a interval of 5s, so you can just retry you operation at a interval of 5.5s or so. And the delay is customizable, see `ConnectionFactory.setRecoveryDelayHandler` and `ConnectionFactory.setNetworkRecoveryInterval`;
 - If you want to be notified when connection recovery is completed, you can add a listener to the connection, see `AutorecoveringConnection.addRecoveryListener`;

