As for adding a dependency, I&#39;m afraid the java.util.Date &amp; .Calendar really are so bad that the first thing I do to any new project is add the Joda-Time library. In Java 8 you can use the new java.time package, inspired by Joda-Time.

The core of Joda-Time is the [`DateTime`][1] class. Unlike java.util.Date, it understands its assigned time zone ([`DateTimeZone`][2]). When converting from j.u.Date, assign a zone.

